OL,3,CHolidays 'top spending priority' for
OL,4,Chouseholds, survey finds
OL,6,FNearly half (46%) of people surveyed
OL,7,Fvoted holidays a top spending
OL,8,Fpriority, ahead of spending on
OL,9,Fclothes, shoes and accessories (35%),
OL,10,Feating and drinking out (33%), home
OL,11,Fand garden renovations (32%) and
OL,12,Fleisure activities (25%).
OL,14,FPeople were able to choose up to three
OL,15,Fspending priorities in the research.
