OL,3,CHolidays 'top spending priority' for
OL,4,Chouseholds, survey finds
OL,6,FThe survey, commissioned by Travel
OL,7,FCounsellors, found even those surveyed
OL,8,Fwho see themselves as "disciplined"
OL,9,Fsavers and rarely treat themselves see
OL,10,Fholidays as a priority, with almost
OL,11,Ftwo-fifths (39%) agreeing.
OL,13,FWhen asked about broader financial
OL,14,Fgoals, nearly a quarter (22%) of
OL,15,Fpeople surveyed said their top
OL,16,Fambition would be to have enough cash
OL,17,Fto travel the world while just 7%
OL,18,Fcited major life milestones such as a
OL,19,Fwedding.
